**What Are Data Structures in Python?**

Data structures are ways to store, organize, and manage data efficiently so that it can be used easily in a program.

**Think of it like:**

If data is clothes 

Data structure is the cupboard/organizer 

Without proper structure, data becomes messy and hard to work with.

Why Data Structures Matter

**They help you:**

Store multiple values

Access data quickly

Modify data easily

Write efficient programs

Handle real-world data
